      \field{abstract}{The Future Circular Collider (FCC-ee) is a leading candidate for Europe’s next major particle accelerator, aimed at achieving unprecedented luminosity to enable precise studies of the Z, W, and H bosons and the top quark. However, it faces major design and operational challenges, especially from collective effects like space charge and wake fields. The FCC-IS Feasibility Study united experts to tackle these issues. This paper reviews the latest progress on collective effects in the FCC-ee main ring and booster, and outlines strategies to mitigate related instabilities.}
      \field{title}{Impact of collective effects on beam stability in the {FCC}-ee main rings and the high-energy booster}
